A3 INSTALL GUIDE

Current public deployment (for this submission attempt)
- Frontend URL: https://eb9bef96b421e8.lhr.life
- Backend URL: https://4bf2a0ae942fd3.lhr.life
- Note: these are SSH reverse tunnels and may expire if the host process stops.

Environment used
- OS: Ubuntu 24.04 LTS (or similar Linux VM)
- Node.js: 20.x LTS
- npm: bundled with Node
- Web server: Nginx

Project layout
- backend/: Express + Prisma + SQLite API server
- frontend/: Vite React app

1. Required packages
- nodejs
- npm
- nginx

Ubuntu example
- sudo apt update
- sudo apt install -y nodejs npm nginx

2. Backend setup
- cd A3/backend
- npm install
- npx prisma generate
- npx prisma db push
- npm run seed

Run backend locally (example port 3000)
- node src/server.js 3000

Notes
- Seeded credentials use password: 123123
- Seed script creates required testing data for regular users, businesses, admins, position types, jobs, qualifications, interests, and negotiations.

3. Frontend setup
- cd A3/frontend
- npm install

For local development (default Vite port 5173)
- npm run dev

Optional API base override
- create file: frontend/.env
- set: VITE_API_BASE=http://localhost:3000

4. Production build and serving

Frontend build
- cd A3/frontend
- npm run build

This creates static files in frontend/dist.

Backend production run
- cd A3/backend
- node src/server.js 3000

5. Nginx reverse proxy + static hosting (single machine)

Example Nginx server block

server {
	listen 80;
	server_name your-domain-or-ip;

	root /absolute/path/to/A3/frontend/dist;
	index index.html;

	location / {
		try_files $uri /index.html;
	}

	location /api/ {
		proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3000/;
		proxy_http_version 1.1;
		proxy_set_header Host $host;
		proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
		proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
	}
}

If using /api prefix in Nginx, set frontend API base accordingly:
- VITE_API_BASE=http://your-domain-or-ip/api

Enable Nginx config and reload
- sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/your-site /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/your-site
- sudo nginx -t
- sudo systemctl reload nginx

6. CORS
- Backend CORS is configured in backend/src/app.js.
- Default allowed frontend origin: http://localhost:5173
- Override via env variable: CORS_ORIGIN

7. Submission/deployment notes
- The SQLite DB and uploaded files are local and can be wiped on redeploy/restart on many PaaS platforms.
- WEBSITE file must contain only the public URL to the deployed site.
- For a stable long-lived URL, deploy backend/frontend to a persistent host (for example Render/Railway/Fly/VM + Nginx).

8. Stable deployment via Render (persistent URL)

This repository now includes `A3/render.yaml` with two services:
- `csc309-a3-backend` (Node web service)
- `csc309-a3-frontend` (static site)

One-time setup in Render dashboard
1. Create a new Blueprint deployment from this repo using `A3/render.yaml`.
2. Wait for first deploy to finish.
3. Copy backend URL from Render, for example: `https://csc309-a3-backend.onrender.com`
4. Set frontend env var:
	- `VITE_API_BASE=https://csc309-a3-backend.onrender.com`
5. Redeploy frontend.
6. Copy frontend URL from Render, for example: `https://csc309-a3-frontend.onrender.com`
7. Set backend env var:
	- `CORS_ORIGIN=https://csc309-a3-frontend.onrender.com`
8. Redeploy backend.
9. Update `A3/WEBSITE` so it contains only the frontend Render URL.

Notes
- Free plans can sleep after inactivity.
- On restart/redeploy, SQLite data may reset depending on Render instance lifecycle.
- If you need persistent database state, switch to managed Postgres and update Prisma datasource.
